["Tverrelvdalen\u00a0(Norwegian)  or Fallijoki\u00a0(Kven)  is a village area in the Tverrelvdalen valley in Alta Municipality in Troms og Finnmark county, Norway.  It is a suburb to the southeast of the town of Alta.  The river Tverrelva runs through the valley and village area.  The 0.4-square-kilometre (99-acre) village has a population (2017) of 430 which gives the village a population density of 1,075 inhabitants per square kilometre (2,780\/sq\u00a0mi).[1]  The Tverrelvdalen IL sports club is based here.[3]","This article about a location in Troms og Finnmark is a stub. You can help Wikipedia by expanding it."]